feat: comprehensive E2E integration tests (Phase 3)

Anchor integration tests for all 5 programs:
- Verifier: VK init, IC point limit, invalid proof rejection
- Nullifier: manager init, register, double-spend, v2 registration, epoch finalize
- Bridge: init, publish/receive epoch root, lock/unlock, admin controls
- Compliance: init, oracle, disclosure, revoke, wealth proof, deactivate

Full-flow E2E test (7 stages):
  Pool init -> 5 deposits -> Merkle root update -> Nullifier mgmt
  -> Bridge -> Compliance -> Admin controls (pause/unpause)

Rust crate test coverage (48 -> 60 tests):
- stealth.rs: stealth_receive match/reject, unique ephemeral keys
- note.rs: Note::new random blinding, nullifier key divergence
- keys.rs: SpendingKey::from_bytes roundtrip, random uniqueness
- commitment.rs: deposit_commitment, hash_pair non-commutativity
- tree: Merkle proof verification, next_index/depth accessors
